### English Title:
U.S. State Department: Wheat Shipment to Yemen "Will Not Go to Waste"

### English Text Summary:
The U.S. State Department stated that a wheat shipment heading to southern Yemen will not be wasted, responding to concerns about potential spoilage or theft due to recent cuts in humanitarian aid funding by the Trump administration. The shipment, which left Oregon in early April, is expected to arrive in mid-May. However, it remains unclear whether the ship will change its destination or if the wheat will be offloaded in Yemen before being sent elsewhere. The State Department did not clarify the funding sources for ensuring the wheat reaches those in need, as contracts with the U.S. Agency for International Development and the World Food Program remain canceled. The article highlights the severe food insecurity in Yemen and the impact of funding cuts on humanitarian efforts.

